OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1780434670
OL,3,CBurrows denies 'toxic atmosphere'
OL,4,Cunder his leadership of UUP
OL,6,FIn his first broadcast interview since
OL,7,FDoug Beattie resigned from the party,
OL,8,FJon Burrows has denied that there is a
OL,9,F'toxic atmosphere' within the UUP
OL,10,Funder his leadership.
OL,12,FSpeaking to UTV's Political Editor
OL,13,FTracey Magee, Jon Burrows said he was
OL,14,F'disappointed by the circumstances' in
OL,15,Fwhich Mr Beattie left the party,
OL,16,Fadding that his leadership is 'not
OL,17,Factually about bringing any kind of
OL,18,Ftoxic atmosphere' and that he believes
OL,19,F'everyone has a voice in the Ulster
OL,20,FUnionist Party.'
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
