FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1780434670
OL,3,CBurrows denies 'toxic atmosphere'
OL,4,Cunder his leadership of UUP
OL,6,FIn a letter posted on social media on
OL,7,FSunday, the Upper Bann MLA resigned
OL,8,Ffrom the party, citing issues with the
OL,9,Fcurrent leadership, saying that MLAs
OL,10,Fwere 'increasingly marginalised.'
OL,12,FMr Beattie, who intends to stay on as
OL,13,Fan independent unionist MLA for Upper
OL,14,FBann, said "an insidious campaign of
OL,15,Frumour and gossip was being waged"
OL,16,Fagainst him, in a scathing letter
OL,17,Faddressed to current party leader, Jon
OL,18,FBurrows.
OL,26,@vD@LOUwD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1780434670
OL,3,CBurrows denies 'toxic atmosphere'
OL,4,Cunder his leadership of UUP
OL,6,FIn his extensive interview with UTV,
OL,7,FMr Burrows said he would not normally
OL,8,Fdiscuss party disciplinary matters in
OL,9,Fpublic, but explained that there was a
OL,10,Fthird-party complaint against Mr
OL,11,FBeattie regarding a historical social
OL,12,Fmedia post.
OL,14,FIn 2022, then leader Doug Beattie
OL,15,Fpublicly apologised when old tweets he
OL,16,Fhad posted were branded misogynistic.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1780434670
OL,3,CBurrows denies 'toxic atmosphere'
OL,4,Cunder his leadership of UUP
OL,6,FJon Burrows said: "There was a third-
OL,7,Fparty complaint that a grossly
OL,8,Fmisogynistic tweet that objectified a
OL,9,Fwoman and compared her to a used car
OL,10,Fwas still on Doug's timeline and had
OL,11,Fnot be deleted, and when I spoke to
OL,12,FDoug about that, it still wasn't
OL,13,Fdeleted several days later."
OL,15,FBurrows also had concerns about a
OL,16,Fclaim made by Mr Beattie that he had
OL,17,Fcanvassed with two councillors, which
OL,18,Fhe later admitted was not true.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1780434670
OL,3,CBurrows denies 'toxic atmosphere'
OL,4,Cunder his leadership of UUP
OL,6,F"I think the public have a right to
OL,7,Fknow that if a senior MLA, who's our
OL,8,Fjustice spokesman, says something
OL,9,Fcategorically in public, that it is
OL,10,Ftrue. That it is not right to say
OL,11,Fthat, beside me are two councillors
OL,12,FI'm canvassing with, and that it is
OL,13,Fsimply untrue. It is a falsehood."
OL,15,FWhen asked about claims that UUP MLA's
OL,16,Fhad raised concerns about their mental
OL,17,Fhealth, the party leader said: "I have
OL,18,Fa small group of MLAs. It would be
OL,19,Fentirely wrong for me to confirm or
OL,20,Fdispel that someone has been talking
OL,21,Fabout their own mental health.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1780434670
OL,3,CBurrows denies 'toxic atmosphere'
OL,4,Cunder his leadership of UUP
OL,6,F"I do not believe it was appropriate
OL,7,Fwhatsoever for a public statement to
OL,8,Fbe made about other colleagues' mental
OL,9,Fhealth. I think that was
OL,10,Funprofessional."
OL,12,FMr Burrows, a former PSNI officer,
OL,13,Fbecame an MLA in 2025 when he was co-
OL,14,Fopted into a seat in North Antrim and
OL,15,Fwas ratified as party leader in
OL,16,FJanuary this year.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1780434670
OL,3,CBurrows denies 'toxic atmosphere'
OL,4,Cunder his leadership of UUP
OL,6,FMr Burrows insisted that he has
OL,7,F'strong support' across the party:
OL,8,F"There's been discussion about issues
OL,9,Fwith MLAs, and there's a
OL,10,Fresponsibility on anyone who's in the
OL,11,Fleadership position to listen, to
OL,12,Freflect, to go make work and make
OL,13,Fthings better."
OL,15,FThere had been speculation in recent
OL,16,Fweeks that some within the party did
OL,17,Fnot want to see Mr Beattie selected to
OL,18,Frun as a candidate in the Upper Bann
OL,19,Fconstituency ` where he has had a seat
OL,20,Ffor 10 years ` at the next election in
OL,21,F2027.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1780434670
OL,3,CBurrows denies 'toxic atmosphere'
OL,4,Cunder his leadership of UUP
OL,6,FThe ex-Army captain said it had become
OL,7,Fclear to him that his position within
OL,8,Fthe party "is no longer tenable".
OL,10,F"Over the last 12 years, I have made
OL,11,Fmany valued friendships within the
OL,12,Fparty, and I sincerely hope those
OL,13,Ffriendships endure," Mr Beattie wrote.
OL,15,F"However, over the past two years I
OL,16,Fhave witnessed a marked deterioration
OL,17,Fin the relationship between the party
OL,18,Fmanagement board, constituency
OL,19,Fassociations, the Ulster Unionist
OL,20,FCouncillor Association, and the MLA
OL,21,Fgroup at Stormont.
OL,26,@pD@KOUpD@`O]rD@AOUuD@TO]wD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1780434670
OL,3,CBurrows denies 'toxic atmosphere'
OL,4,Cunder his leadership of UUP
OL,6,F"This became particularly apparent and
OL,7,Faccelerated following your election as
OL,8,Fparty leader when MLAs were
OL,9,Fincreasingly marginalised, ignored,
OL,10,Fisolated and discredited.
OL,12,F"Your leadership style became
OL,13,Fdismissive and overly centralised,
OL,14,Fempowering individuals to actively
OL,15,Fundermine elected representatives," he
OL,16,Fsaid.
OL,18,F"In the absence of any coherent policy
OL,19,Fdirection from the leadership, a toxic
OL,20,Fatmosphere has been allowed to
OL,21,Fflourish within the party.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUwD@cO]zD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1780434670
OL,3,CBurrows denies 'toxic atmosphere'
OL,4,Cunder his leadership of UUP
OL,6,F"The Ulster Unionist Party once prided
OL,7,Fitself on its social conscience, its
OL,8,Fprogressive and moderate outlook, and
OL,9,Fits respected conservative tradition.
OL,11,F"I no longer believe that is the case
OL,12,Fand I no longer feel at home or
OL,13,Fcomfortable within the party."
OL,15,FHe added: "Even as I raised concerns
OL,16,Fdirectly with you, an insidious
OL,17,Fcampaign of rumour and gossip was
OL,18,Fbeing waged against me regarding
OL,19,Fselections, party relationships,
OL,20,Ffinancial matters, and employment
OL,21,Fissues."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUuD@^O]wD@KOU}D@HO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
